(lp295
VThis document is the root Software Requirements Specification for GHOST.\u000a\u000aGHOST means GenAI Hybrid Orchestrator for Software Tooling.\u000a\u000aGHOST is a human-controlled AI orchestration platform for software engineering. It combines deterministic and heuristic context-engineering methods with LLM-based agents, project retrieval, reusable engineering memory, and external AI tooling in one controlled workflow.\u000a\u000aThis root SRS defines the product-level scope, professional SRS structure, root requirement anchors, naming policy, traceability direction, current-vs-future boundary, and proposed child-file ownership map for the future StrictDoc requirement tree.\u000a\u000aThis root SRS is not intended to repeat every detailed subsystem requirement. Detailed atomic requirements shall live in child StrictDoc files after explicit human approval of the requirement-file tree and source-of-truth cutover.\u000a
p296
asg263
V>>>\u000a
