(lp415
VThe current GHOST scope covers:\u000a\u000a- engineered prompt construction,\u000a- deterministic preprocessing,\u000a- prompt shaping,\u000a- SuperPrompt state management,\u000a- current GUI-visible prompt rendering through SuperPromptProjector,\u000a- project document ingestion,\u000a- project document retrieval,\u000a- document reranking,\u000a- A3 usefulness gating,\u000a- A4 context condensation,\u000a- reusable engineering memory,\u000a- optional memory retrieval inside the current Retrieval stage,\u000a- memory merge and ActiveBrief direction,\u000a- GUI-based human control,\u000a- structured logging direction,\u000a- AWS-compatible runtime deployment,\u000a- future requirement-architecture-code-test traceability direction.\u000a\u000aThe root SRS distinguishes current executable behavior from target architecture and future vision.\u000a\u000aThe conceptual target pipeline is:\u000a\u000aA0_PreProcessing -> A2_PromptShaper -> Retrieval -> ReRanker -> A3_NLI_Gate -> A4_Condenser -> A5_Format_Enforcer -> Prompt_Builder\u000a\u000aThe current executable GUI runner is more limited:\u000a\u000aPreProcessing -> A2 -> Retrieval -> ReRanker or pass-through -> A3 -> A4\u000a\u000aCurrent final prompt rendering is performed through SuperPromptProjector and SuperPrompt prompt-ready composition. The dedicated Prompt Builder/send-boundary remains incomplete and shall not be described as fully implemented.\u000a
p416
asg263
