VGHOST:\u000aGenAI Hybrid Orchestrator for Software Tooling. The product name.\u000a\u000aragstream/:\u000aThe current legacy Python package directory inside the repository. It is an implementation namespace, not the product identity. New requirement language shall use GHOST as the product name.\u000a\u000aRAGstream:\u000aHistorical product/repository wording in older documents. Existing pre-cutover documents may still contain this name as legacy evidence. New or migrated StrictDoc requirements shall use GHOST unless specifically referring to legacy naming.\u000a\u000aSuperPrompt:\u000aThe central structured runtime representation of the current task, prompt configuration, selected document context, memory context, stage state, diagnostics, and prompt-ready rendering.\u000a\u000aSuperPromptProjector:\u000aThe current component responsible for GUI-visible engineered prompt rendering and prompt-ready composition.\u000a\u000aController:\u000aThe orchestration component that owns the active SuperPrompt for a session, runs legal pipeline stages, manages project context, and returns updated state to the GUI.\u000a\u000aAgent Stack:\u000aThe JSON-configured agent infrastructure consisting of AgentFactory, AgentPrompt, llm_client, structured output parsing, and executable agent modes.\u000a\u000aAgentFactory:\u000aThe component that loads and validates agent configuration and creates concrete agent prompt objects.\u000a\u000aAgentPrompt:\u000aThe neutral prompt-composition component that combines static agent purpose, enum catalogs, runtime payload, and task instructions.\u000a\u000allm_client:\u000aThe LLM provider abstraction currently used for external model API calls and intended to keep model-provider details out of Controller and GUI code.\u000a\u000aExecutable AgentPrompt modes:\u000aThe current executable compose modes are selector, classifier, and synthesizer. Chooser and multi-chooser are aliases or design vocabulary mapped into current executable modes. Writer and Extractor shall not be claimed as live compose modes unless supported by child requirements and code evidence.\u000a\u000aA0:\u000aDeterministic preprocessing stage.\u000a\u000aA2:\u000aPromptShaper stage that selects prompt meta-settings such as system role, audience, tone, depth, and confidence.\u000a\u000aA3:\u000aUsefulness gate stage for retrieved document candidates and comparison context.\u000a\u000aA4:\u000aContext condenser stage for selected document evidence.\u000a\u000aA5:\u000aFormat Enforcer direction. It is reserved/postponed and has no completed live controller action in the current executable runner.\u000a\u000aPrompt Builder:\u000aTarget final prompt-assembly/send-boundary concept. The dedicated prompt_builder.py path is not the current complete rendering authority. Current visible rendering is through SuperPromptProjector.\u000a\u000aHard Rules:\u000aPlanned governance/enforcement direction. Current code contains placeholders and UI/status direction, not a completed hard-rule engine.\u000a\u000aDirect LLM Call:\u000aOptional future send-boundary direction. Current supported core path is engineered prompt generation and display, with manual copy/use in external tools.\u000a\u000aDocument Knowledge:\u000aThe document ingestion, retrieval, reranking, evidence-selection, and document-condensation capability area.\u000a\u000aMemory System:\u000aThe durable memory recording, memory ingestion, memory retrieval, ActiveBrief, memory merge, and memory file/import capability area.\u000a\u000aActiveBrief:\u000aA compact memory or topic-direction artifact used to guide memory-related retrieval, relation classification, or comparison-context construction.\u000a\u000aMemoryRecord:\u000aA durable recorded memory unit stored through the memory system.\u000a\u000aUID:\u000aStable unique requirement identifier.\u000a\u000aStrictDoc:\u000aThe requirements documentation system used for the future requirement source-of-truth tree.\u000a\u000aGhost2:\u000aFuture product vision for human-mediated multi-brain orchestration, shared board behavior, shared memory, and deterministic requirement-architecture-code-test traceability.\u000a\u000aAWS:\u000aAmazon Web Services runtime environment used by the current deployment direction.\u000a\u000aEC2:\u000aAWS Elastic Compute Cloud runtime host.\u000a\u000aECR:\u000aAWS Elastic Container Registry used for Docker image storage.\u000a\u000aSSM Parameter Store:\u000aAWS secret/configuration storage direction for runtime secrets.\u000a\u000anginx:\u000aReverse proxy used in the documented AWS deployment path.\u000a\u000aChromaDB:\u000aVector-store technology used by the document and memory retrieval directions.\u000a\u000aSPLADE:\u000aSparse retrieval technique used in the documented hybrid retrieval direction.\u000a\u000aColBERT:\u000aReranking/retrieval improvement direction. It shall not be assumed as implemented or superior without evaluation evidence.\u000a
p506
