VGHOST is organized as a modular orchestration system. The main workflow connects user input, project knowledge, engineering memory, deterministic control logic, LLM-based agents, external AI tooling, and deployment infrastructure into one inspectable engineering process.\u000a\u000aAt the highest level, GHOST contains:\u000a\u000a- a Streamlit GUI,\u000a- an orchestration Controller,\u000a- a SuperPrompt runtime state model,\u000a- SuperPromptProjector prompt-ready rendering,\u000a- a document knowledge pipeline,\u000a- a configurable Agent Stack,\u000a- project document stores,\u000a- memory stores,\u000a- structured logging direction,\u000a- local runtime support,\u000a- AWS deployment infrastructure.\u000a\u000aThe architecture separates document ingestion and retrieval, memory recording and retrieval, prompt shaping and context construction, customizable agents, hard-rule direction, logging and observability, deployment, runtime persistence, and future traceability synchronization.\u000a
