(lp753
VSuperPrompt is the authoritative in-memory state for the current run. It contains normalized prompt fields, stage state, retrieval views, selected chunk IDs, condensed context, memory context, attachments, diagnostics, and GUI-visible prompt-ready rendering.\u000a\u000aThe Controller owns the active SuperPrompt for a session, calls pipeline stages in legal order, updates stage/history fields, manages active project context, and avoids absorbing retrieval logic, embedding logic, LLM-provider logic, or GUI rendering responsibility.\u000a\u000aDocument stores and memory stores are controlled data domains.\u000a\u000aDocument ingestion produces chunks, stable IDs, metadata, embeddings, sparse representations where enabled, manifests, and persistent stores.\u000a\u000aMemory recording produces durable MemoryRecords and metadata. Memory ingestion and retrieval work from durable memory truth without replacing it.\u000a\u000aThe memory truth split is:\u000a\u000a- .ragmem stores stable memory body content,\u000a- .ragmeta.json stores editable metadata mirror,\u000a- SQLite stores query/index metadata.\u000a\u000aMemory vectors, ActiveBriefs, compression outputs, and runtime MemoryContextPacks shall not replace durable memory truth.\u000a
