VThe current implementation baseline includes:\u000a\u000a- Streamlit GUI structure,\u000a- prompt input and engineered prompt display,\u000a- current runner through A4,\u000a- runtime log display,\u000a- project selection,\u000a- project-based ingestion controls,\u000a- deterministic preprocessing,\u000a- JSON-based Agent Stack,\u000a- A2 PromptShaper,\u000a- A3 usefulness gate,\u000a- A4 condenser,\u000a- SuperPrompt shared state,\u000a- SuperPromptProjector prompt-ready rendering,\u000a- project document ingestion,\u000a- hybrid retrieval backbone,\u000a- composite Retrieval stage with document retrieval and optional memory retrieval,\u000a- document-only ReRanker behavior,\u000a- AWS Phase-1 deployment direction,\u000a- TextForge/RagLog logging direction,\u000a- memory recording,\u000a- memory ingestion,\u000a- memory retrieval,\u000a- server-side memory files,\u000a- ChatGPT shared-link import,\u000a- ActiveBrief relation classification,\u000a- runtime MemoryMerge synthesis.\u000a\u000aThe following areas are incomplete, postponed, optional, placeholder, or future:\u000a\u000a- dedicated final Prompt Builder/send-boundary,\u000a- prompt_builder.py as complete final assembly authority,\u000a- A5 Format Enforcer live controller action,\u000a- full Hard Rules enforcement,\u000a- Direct LLM Call as completed send-boundary,\u000a- full observability/metrics dashboard,\u000a- logger production hardening,\u000a- multi-user support,\u000a- Blackboard Actor persistence,\u000a- automatic requirement-architecture-code synchronization,\u000a- ColBERT/reranking improvement as evaluated future topic.\u000a\u000aThe root SRS shall preserve the distinction between implemented behavior, documented design, planned near-term work, optional experiments, placeholders, and future vision.\u000a
