ders, upload limits, and prompt-only mode proposal.\u000a  |\u000a  |-- 60_runtime_operations.sdoc                  [CHILD]\u000a  |   `-- Local/AWS runtime, Docker, EC2, ECR, nginx, HTTPS, Route53, SSM, and persistent runtime data.\u000a  |\u000a  |-- 70_quality_governance.sdoc                  [CHILD]\u000a  |   `-- Testing, logging, evaluation, security hardening, operational monitoring, component cards, source-of-truth governance, and change control.\u000a  |\u000a  |-- 80_requirement_traceability_direction.sdoc  [CHILD/FUTURE]\u000a  |   `-- Stable UID mapping direction for requirements, architecture, code, tests, code-side UID markers, and future synchronization-agent support.\u000a  |\u000a  `-- 90_future_vision_backlog.sdoc               [FUTURE]\u000a      `-- Ghost2, future hard-rule expansion, future model/tool routing, and backlog items not yet active requirements.\u000a\u000aOwnership rule:\u000a\u000aThe root SRS shall remain readable and navigable. It shall define root anchors and ownership boundaries. Detailed atomic requirements shall be migrated into proposed child files only after human approval of the tree.\u000a
